    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-05-07T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-05-07T04:00:00-05:00" n="155"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/801: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-07T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 7, 1928—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 7—7:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>318. Tsingtau reports arrival of mail from Price<note n="40" xml:id="d155fn40"
                        >Ernest B. Price, consul at Tsinan.</note> this morning by Japanese military
                    train and that up to May 6, 6 a.m. it was believed that no Americans were
                    injured or American property looted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
